ch of `a`\n- **end** the index of the matching `b`\n- **pre** the preamble, `a` and `b` not included\n- **body** the match, `a` and `b` not included\n- **post** the postscript, `a` and `b` not included\n\nIf there's no match, `undefined` will be returned.\n\nIf the `str` contains more `a` than `b` / there are unmatched pairs, the first match that was closed will be used. For example, `{{a}` will match `['{', 'a', '']` and `{a}}` will match `['', 'a', '}']`.\n\n### const r = balanced.range(a, b, str)\n\nFor the first non-nested matching pair of `a` and `b` in `str`, return an\narray with indexes: `[ <a index>, <b index> ]`.\n\nIf there's no match, `undefined` will be returned.\n\nIf the `str` contains more `a` than `b` / there are unmatched pairs, the first match that was closed will be used. For example, `{{a}` will match `[ 1, 3 ]` and `{a}}` will match `[0, 2]`.\n","_id":"@isaacs/balanced-match","versions":{"4.0.0":{"tshy":{"exports":{".":"./src/index.ts","./package.json":"./package.json"}},"directories":{},"_nodeVersion":"22.14.0","devDependencies":{"mkdirp":"^3.0.1","typedoc":"^0.28.5","prettier":"^3.3.2","@types/node":"^24.0.0","@types/brace-expansion":"^1.1.2","tap":"^21.1.0","tshy":"^3.0.2"},"license":"MIT","maintainers":[{"name":"isaacs","email":"i@izs.me"}],"homepage":"https://github.com/juliangruber/balanced-match","type":"module","engines":{"node":"20 || >=22"},"exports":{".":{"import":{"types":"./dist/esm/index.d.ts","default":"./dist/esm/index.js"},"require":{"types":"./dist/commonjs/index.d.ts","default":"./dist/commonjs/index.js"}},"./package.json":"./package.json"},"prettier":{"useTabs":false,"endOfLine":"lf","jsxSingleQuote":false,"bracketSameLine":true,"semi":false,"tabWidth":2,"printWidth":80,"arrowParens":"avoid","singleQuote":true},"repository":{"url":"git://github.com/juliangruber/balanced-match.git","type":"git"},"name":"@isaacs/balanced-match","_id":"@isaacs/balanced-match@4.0.0","gitHead":"666d35f9e3015a1dac69d7d7c5de330cbd5fc39a","scripts":